rComments: Honestly a funny prof. He cares about his students and their success. Attend lectures and take good notes and you will do great. Participation also matters so make sure to talk and answer questions. The exams were super easy because they were actually about the lectures and the review questions he gives are very helpful. He's very accommodating too

He is one of the most knowledgeable profs when it comes to Arabic language, history, & culture. Participation matters, it's for your own good to attend because there r things he points out that r important. Made me love Arabic even more&made me eager to advance in it. Supportive and accessible, clearly cares about his students. Textbook needed.
He's the sweetest prof I've met at uOttawa. Hilarious, lets us leave class early, and I took 2 classes with him- I hope to take more classes with him in the future
This was a very easy course to take although, his lectures are not very organized. Sometimes he can get off-topic very quickly but all in all, it was a good mark booster.
Enjoyed taking his Arabic classes. Very kind and dedicated to the field of teaching. Very approachable, a quality hard to find in many university profs.

Professor Basam is the best. He is a very flexible and caring prof. He listens to students' feedback. His lessons are hard and advanced, but he takes time to explain if you need it. Very good group atmosphere, and everyone has chances to speak and contribute. He tells good stories! Very knowledgeable about the Arabic language and culture.

Easily one of the best professors at Uottawa. One of the easiest classes I've taken. The prof is kind and caring for his students. He gives the questions and answers a week prior to the midterms. All MC, and all you gotta do is study them. Final report paper was quite easy as he reduced it to two pages due to pandemic. Great prof overall!
Great guy. Even if you don't do well, he'll help you bump up your grade. Yes, the course is quite condensed but if you keep up, you'll be more than fine.

prof was unorganized, did not teach thorough lessons. His teaching was scattered around and he didn't get to every unit, though he tried to speed through them and get everything on the exam. His lectures were hard to follow and he went on extreme tangents. It's not only his fault; it's the school's language exam. did not follow the rules.
